SGF format basics:
- Starts with `(`
- Contains nodes starting with `;`
- Each node has properties like `KEY[value]`
- Properties can have multiple values: `KEY[val1][val2]`
- Children/variations are enclosed in `(...)`: `(...)`
- Ends with `)`
- Example: `(;FF[4]C[root]SZ[19];B[aa];W[ab])`

